fields: There's no helping it. This was too much for her to handle alone.
But she came here knowing that.
But... that's too much! This can't be right!
If she gives up, it's over.
But you have the power to change fate itself...
All this inevitable destruction and tragedy... You can change it, if you want.
The power to do so lies within you. Can I really?
Can I really do something to help?
Could I really change this ending?
Of course you could. So make a contract with me...
It was all just a dream?
Is Mom up? Tatsuya's waking her up right now.
Go help him, will you? Okay!
So what's been going on lately?
That's the second one this month.
Boys who don't even have the guts to confess their love in person are no good.
It seems like Ms. Saotome's new relationship is going well.
She gushes about him all during homeroom.
It'll be their 3-month anniversary this week, so I guess that's a new record.
Hmm, I guess we'll see. They're reaching a crucial juncture right now.
If it's not the real thing, it's around this point in the relationship that things start falling apart.
Well, if they make it past 3 months, they're probably good a year at least.
Huh? But isn't this too flashy?
That's at LEAST as flashy as you should be!
A woman's appearance is the one thing she can't afford to get looked down at.
That should make all your secret admirers melt in adoration.
I don't have any secret admirers!
But you should go about as though you do. That's the secret behind every pretty girl's success!
There, eat it all up now, okay? Okay!
Now then, you'd better hurry too, Madoka.
Have a nice day, sweetie! Have nice daaaay!
Oh! Cute ribbons! You think so? They're not too flashy? I think they look lovely.
So my mom said... A boy who confesses his love with a letter instead of in person is no good.
Your mom is just too cool, Madoka!
I mean, she's gorgeous and a successful businesswoman besides!
If only I could make up my mind to reject a boy so easily.
What an enviable problem to have!
It really is! I wish I could get a love letter from someone too.
Just once! Oh-ho! So you want to become a beautiful, popular girl like Hitomi, Madoka?
And you've decided to start changing your image with these hair ribbons, huh?
You've got it wrong! My mom made me- I see! You even got your mom to tell you the secret to becoming popular!
How shameless! Let me show you what happens to bad girls like you!
But I won't allow you to go off and become popular with the boys.
You must be my bride, Madoka!!
Ahem! Now, I have something very important to discuss with you today, class. I want you all to listen very closely!
When frying an egg, should it be fried sunny side-up or over hard?!
Huh?! U-um, well- Th-they can be fried either way, can't they?
They can be fried either way!
And it should go without saying... ...that judging a woman's attractiveness... ...by the way she fries her eggs is the gravest of mistakes!
I want you to remember... ...that you must never date men who insist they can't eat fried eggs done over hard.
And boys- You'd better not grow up so petty as to fuss over how your eggs are done, okay?
Well, then! Now that that's out of the way, let's welcome our new transfer student!
Hey, shouldn't that have come first?
Now, then! Why don't you tell your classmates about yourself?
My name is Homura Akemi. Pleased to meet you.
So, Miss Akemi... What school did you come from?
Did you do any club activities at your old school?
How about sports? Or cultural activities?
I didn't participate in activities. Your hair is so beautiful!
What kind of shampoo do you use?
She has a mysterious air to her, doesn't she?
Hey, Madoka, do you know that girl?
Maybe it was just me, but it seemed like she was glaring at you earlier. Well... Um...
I think today's been a little stressful for me. I'm not feeling very well.
Would you allow me to excuse myself to the Nurse's Office?
Oh! Then let me show you the way there. I'll come too!
No, you needn't trouble yourselves. I'll ask the Nurse's Aide to take me.
Miss Madoka Kaname. You are the Nurse's Aide for this class, are you not?
May I ask you to accompany me? To the Nurse's Office, that is.
How did you know I was the Nurse's Aide?
Oh, um, the Nurse's Office is...
This way, isn't it? Yes, that's right.
Um, but... um... It seems like you already know how to get there...
What is it? Oh, um... That's kind of an unusual name, isn't it?
O-oh! But not in a bad way! I-I was just thinking it sounded kind of cool-
Madoka Kaname. Do you treasure the life you currently live?
Do you consider your family and friends precious?
Both my family and my friends-
I love all of them, and consider them very precious!
Do you really? Yes, really! I couldn't lie about that.
If that's really the case, then you wouldn't try to change the person you currently are, would you?
Because if you do, you will end up losing all of those things.
...Huh? You should stay as you are, Madoka Kaname.
Stay as you are, and as you always shall be.
D-did she just break the prefecture-wide record..?
It doesn't make any sense, does it?
Just when I was thinking she was someone gifted with both brains and beauty...
...it turns out she's a crazy New Age weirdo!
Exactly how far was she going to keep up that weirdo character act?
Is that what gets her MOE?! How the heck is that even exciting?!
Madoka, are you sure you've never met Miss Akemi before?
Hmm... Well, the sensible answer is, "yes," but...
What's that supposed to mean? That you have met her before in some "insensible" way?
Well... Last night... I first met her... in a dream... Or something.
Awesome! You're acting like you're a anime character, too!
That's mean! This is really bugging me!
You must have known each other in a previous life, and were brought by fate across time and space to meet once again!
You said you met in a dream. What kind of dream was it?
It was... To be honest, I can't really remember anymore.
I do know that it was a really strange dream, though...
Then maybe you actually have met Miss Akemi somewhere before.
Huh?! Though you may not consciously remember, your subconscious could have taken note of her...
...and later brought her image out in a dream.
Isn't that a little far-fetched? I mean, that's some coincidence!
I suppose. Oh! It's already this late?
Piano lessons, right? Or is it Japanese classical dance today?
Even though Entrance Exams are right around the corner. I wonder how long Mother intends to make me continue with them.
Whew! Makes me glad I wasn't born rich. Should we get going too?
Madoka, do you mind if we stopped at the music store on the way home?
That's fine. Buying another CD for Kamijo? Sort of.
Well, see you later. Bye-bye! Later!
No! Please, don't do something cruel!
This has nothing to do with you.
I could hear him begging me to save him! ...I see.
Now she's attacking people in cosplay?!
And what is that thing? It's not a stuffed animal, is it? It's alive?
I don't know. I don't know what any of this is. But we have to save him!
Huh?! Where'd the exit go? What is this place?!
There's something wrong with this place. The path keeps changing!
This has got to be a joke, right? I mean, I must be dreaming, right?
What is..? That was close! But you're safe now.
Oh! You rescued Kyubey for me, didn't you?
Thank you. He's a dear friend of mine.
I-I was called to him. I heard his voice inside my head.
Those uniforms... You must be students at Mitakihara Middle School too.
Who are you? That's right, I haven't introduced myself yet.
...mind if I wrap up a bit of work?
If you want to finish it off, you'd better go after it right now.
I'll let you take it this time.
You don't read between the lines very well, do you? I'm telling you I'll overlook what you did this time.
Don't you think it would be better for both of us not to court needless trouble?
You're a lifesaver. If you want to thank anyone, it should be these two. I was just passing by.
Thank you very much. My name is Kyubey.
Were you the one who was calling me?
And you, Sayaka Miki. How do you know our names?
I came here because I have a request for you two.
I want you to make contracts with me and become magical girls!
I will grant you one wish- any wish you desire!
Anything you want. I can grant you even the most impossible of miracles!
I'm a third-year student at Mitakihara Middle School.
And... ...I am one who has made a contract with Kyubey - a magical girl!
Madoka... I heard you got in late last night?
Yeah, I got invited over to an older student's house...
Well, I'm not going to make a fuss about curfews or anything, let us know where you are before dinner, all right?
I live here alone, so feel free to make yourselves comfortable.
Though I'm afraid I don't have much to offer as refreshments...
Oh, Mami! This is so delicious!
Since you two have been chosen by Kyubey as well, it means you are now involved in all of this.
So I thought there were a few things we should go over.
Right, right! Feel free to ask us anything you want!
Sayaka... I think you've got it backwards...
When Kyubey makes a contract with a girl, a Soul Gem is born.
It is the source of our magic, and also the proof that we are magical girls.
I will grant you one wish- any wish you desire!
I can grant you even the most impossible of miracles!
So we could wish for riches and treasures? Or eternal youth? Or even the fabled 108-dish banquet of the emperors?!
Uh, maybe not that last one...
Yes, but in exchange for that wish, your Soul Gem is created.
Those who possess a Soul Gem are duty-bound to do battle with witches.
Say that someone offered to magically grant you any wish in the world. What would you do?
I'd have those two trustees driven straight out of the company.
The CEO really is getting too old to keep pushing himself, so maybe I'd have him retire?
Oh, but he hasn't named a successor yet...
Then what if you became the new CEO?
If I could gather enough support in the Sales Department...
I've already got the Planning Committee and General Affairs in my corner...
Then my only hurdle would be old Baldy from the Accounting Department... Maybe... Interesting...
Mom... You've got a scary look in your eyes...
So what exactly is a witch? Are they different from magical girls?
If magical girls can be said to be born from wishes, then witches are creatures born from curses.
Just as magical girls spread hope to the world, witches spread despair.
And since they're invisible to regular humans, it makes their evil all the more insidious.
Anxiety and mistrust... Irrational rage and hatred...
They sow the seeds of disaster throughout the world.
Many of the inexplicable suicides and murders that occur...
Its formless darkness grows within the cursed human... ...until it consumes him from the inside out.
If these witches are so dangerous, why don't people know about them yet?
Because witches hide themselves deep within the labyrinths they create...
and take care never to appear before human eyes.
That maze-like place you wandered into today was a labyrinth.
Humans who stray into them usually don't make it out alive.
And you fight such scary creatures?
Yes, often at the risk of my life.
That's why you two... should think very carefully before deciding to become magical girls.
Having been chosen by Kyubey, you have the rare chance to have any wish granted.
But remember that that wish lies side-by-side with death.
Oh, man... This is gonna be a tough choice.
To help you make up your minds, why don't you come along with me on a few witch hunts?
You should see for yourself what it's like to do battle with witches. Also... you should think long and hard...
about whether there's something you want badly enough...
...to make it worth putting yourself in danger.
So other people really can't see him?
O-oh! No, it's nothing at all! L-let's get going!
It seems like we can communicate... ...just by thinking to each other like this.
Wah! What?! You mean we already have magical powers?!
No, no. I'm just acting as an intermediary between your thoughts right now.
But it's handy being able to talk telepathically, isn't it?
Hey, you two. What's going on?
You've been staring so intently into one another's eyes...
Huh? Oh, n-no, there's nothing... going on...
No, don't tell me- You're already close enough to communicate through your eyes alone?!
Ohh!! But for two people to suddenly get that much closer overnight-
What on earth did you do after I left yesterday?!
No, seriously. It totally isn't what you're thinking-
Well, a lot of things did happen last night, but...
But you can't!! You're both girls, after all!
Don't you see that it's a love that can never beeeee?!
Hitomi's acting so much like you today, Sayaka.
Hey! What's that supposed to mean?!
But seriously, is it really okay for you to tag along to school with us?
Like I said, that girl from yesterday just transferred into our class.
Isn't she trying to kill you?
Actually, I think the school is the safest place for me.
But Mami is a third-year student, so her class is pretty far from ours.
Don't worry, I can hear you all perfectly.
At this distance, I can still reach her with my telepathy.
I promise I'll keep close watch over you all, so don't worry.
Anyway, she doesn't strike me as the type who would attack you in public.
So is that transfer student also a...
A magical girl? Just like you, Mami?
Yes, there's no doubt about it. She seems to be a fairly powerful one, too.
But doesn't that mean she's a good guy who also fights against the witches?
So why would she suddenly start attacking Madoka?
It was me that she was after.
It seemed like she was trying to prevent me from contracting a new magical girl.
If we're all fighting the same enemy, wouldn't it be better if there were more of us?
It's actually more common for magical girls to contend against one another.
There are certain rewards one can gain from defeating a witch.
That's why sometimes, depending on the time and situation, Magical girls may actually battle one another for the right to those rewards.
So basically, the reason that girl was staring at Madoka all day yesterday...
...was because she knew Kyubey was trying to get to her?
If she tries anything on you, I'll punch her lights out!
Plus, we have Mami here to protect you too!
That's right. Leaving aside Miki and her punches, I am here, so you will be just fine.
And so... ...the form we've been studying up to this point...
...in which the person or thing performing an action is the subject of the sentence...
...which is what we call a sentence in which "B is et cetera'd by A."
In other words, the subject of the sentence is the recipient of the verb...
...instead of the one performing it. So the form is "be" + the verb in the past participle.
Now let's take the sample sentence, "he likes me."
Hey, Madoka... Have you come up with a wish yet?
I've gone through and considered so many different things too.
I mean, there are plenty of things I want to have or do, but...
...I guess the whole "risking your life for it" part is what's getting me.
None of the stuff I want is worth that much.
How odd. Most of the girls I make my offer to accept right away.
Well... Maybe the pair of us are just fools?
Yep. A pair of blissfully ignorant fools...
I'm sure it's not all that unusual.
Wishing for something so strongly you'd gladly trade your life for it...
There must be countless people in this world... ...who have such wishes in their hearts.
Most likely... It means the two of us who can't even figure out what to wish for...
...haven't experienced even a fraction of those people's suffering.
We've been so blessed... ...that we've become ignorant fools.
There are probably people who would give anything for a chance like this...
Picking up where you left off yesterday?
No. I have no such intention.
I had hoped to kill it before it made contact with Madoka Kaname, but it is too late for that now...
Will you become a magical girl as well?
Like you have any right to ask us anything!
...Do you remember what I said yesterday?
Good. Then I'll pray that my warning will not have been in vain.
What did you wish for when you became a magical girl?
Hitomi! Sorry, but the two of us have a few small errands to run today, so...
I guess there's just no room anymore...
Once again, you've got it totally wrong...
You're finally going to come have coffee with us after school, right?
...I have some urgent business to attend to today as well.
Now, then! Shall we begin Lesson 1 of our little "A Day in the Life of a Magical Girl" class?
I don't know if it'll be any help, but...
I figured it was better than having nothing to defend ourselves with.
Well, I'm glad you're going into this with that kind of mindset.
How about you, Madoka? Bring anything?
I-I thought maybe I should at least start thinking about costume ideas...
Well, you've certainly brought enough enthusiasm!
Well, I can't top that! You totally beat me..!
These are remnants of the magic used by that witch we faced yesterday.
The core of witch-hunting is scouting the city on foot.
Once your Soul Gem picks up a witch's trail, you just follow it until it leads you to the witch.
It's a lot less exciting than I was expecting.
The Gem doesn't seem to be glowing any brighter.
It's because it's been a full night since the witch escaped.
There are fewer footprints around to catch hold of now.
What if you had gone after it right away yesterday?
I may have been able to finish it off.
But it wasn't worth leaving the two of you alone after what you'd been through.
Yep! You truly are an ally of justice, Mami!
On the other hand, what is with that transfer student?! She really pisses me off!
Say, Mami... Do you at least have an idea of where the witch might be?
You often find traces of witches' auras...
That's why I usually check high-traffic streets and spots in the Red Light District...
...where fights tend to break out first.
Also, out-of-the-way places where people might try to commit suicide.
Then, there are hospitals- the most awful places for a witch to take up.
...draining the precious life force... out of those who are already weakened with pain and illness.
It's reacting to some very powerful magic.
No, she's fine. She's only fainted.
I won't let you escape this time!
It's not much, but it should serve to protect you from any immediate dangers at least.
You must stay near me once we're inside, all right?
So? Are you scared yet, you two?
Keep it up! We're almost at the deepest point in the labyrinth!
Y-you're going to fight that thing?
As though I would lose to that!
As though I could let myself look so uncool in front of my future magical girl juniors!
Witches carry them sometimes. If you're lucky, you'll find one after a battle.
It's all right. In this form, they're perfectly safe.
In fact, they're incredibly valuable because of what they can do.
The color of my Soul Gem looks a little muddier now than it did last night, right?
But if I use the Grief Seed...
Right? With this, the magic I expended during the fight is restored as well.
When I said there were certain rewards to defeating witches, I meant this.
It should be good for one more use.
Or do you dislike sharing with others?
It was your kill. You should keep the reward for yourself.
I see. So that's your answer.
Ugh! She really does bug me!
It only works if both parties feel that way.
O-oh my god, what was I about to?
You were just having a bad dream, that's all.
It's too confusing, figuring out what I would wish for...
But Mami looked so amazing when she was fighting to save people...
If even someone like me... ...could go around truly helping people like that...
I only pretend to be cool. I'm really pushing myself hard.
Even when I'm scared, or hurting, there's no one I can talk to.
All I can do is cry on my own.
It isn't a good thing... to be a magical girl.
I'm not afraid of anything anymore.
Really, thank you so much for all of this.
You're really some kind genius at finding rare CDs, aren't you?
Nah! I just get lucky, that's all.
This soloist's interpretations are really incredible.
Do you want to try listening to it too, Sayaka? I-If you don't mind...
I wish I could play this on a speaker for you, but we are in a hospital, after all...
Maaan, you are so cool, Mami!
This isn't a magic show, you know.
Don't forget that what we're doing here is very dangerous.
It didn't drop a Grief Seed this time.
It's because that was only a witch's familiar - not a witch itself.
So that wasn't a witch... It seems like we've only been fighting duds lately.
Yes, but we can't leave familiars to do as they please.
If allowed to develop, familiars become the same kind of witch they broke off from.
So have you figured out what to wish for?
Uh-uh... That's how it goes, once someone tells you to think hard about something.
What did you wish for, Mami?
Oh! I don't mean to pry if you don't want to answer-
...I didn't have the luxury of thinking about it first.
It's not that I have any regrets.
I think the life I currently live... ...is far better than dying in that place would have been.
But... I'd like those who do have the chance to think carefully before deciding.
I want them to have the choice I didn't have.
If you make a wish, does it have to be for yourself?
For example - and this is really just an example, okay?
Say there was someone who was having a way tougher time than I am, and I wanted to make my wish to help him.
I said this was just an example!!
There's no requirement that the wish's beneficiary be the contractee herself.
There's even precedent for it already.
But it may not be the best idea.
If you want to use your wish to grant someone else's, then you must make doubly sure you know what you're wishing for.
Miki, do you truly wish for his dream to come true?
Or do you actually wish to grant his dream so that he will be grateful to you?
Mami..! They sound similar, but they're completely different at the core.
You know? ...That's a little harsh, isn't it?
I'm sorry. But this really needs to be said now, before it's too late.
Because if you go ahead with it without making certain first, you're sure to regret it later.
I guess my idea was a little nave.
Sorry. It really is a hard decision, isn't it?
There's no need to rush into it.
Though for me, the sooner you decide, the better.
That's no good, Kyubey. Nobody likes a boy who pressures girls to do things.
It really isn't an easy decision, is it?
And considering my position, I can't rush you into deciding either.
Suggesting wishes would also be against the rules.
So I guess just wishing to become a magical girl wouldn't work, huh?
Is power for its own sake what you desire, Madoka?
I mean, I'm not very smart, and I don't really have any talents.
So if I could become someone as cool and wonderful as Mami...
...I'd be more than happy with just that.
If you became a magical girl, Madoka, you'd be much more powerful than Mami.
Huh? Though, of course, part of that depends on what kind of wish you make.
Even I can't completely gauge how large the Soul Gem you'd create would be.
I've never met another girl with such enormous potential as you.
You're just teasing me, right? No...
If he wants a drink so badly, he can damn well pour it himself..!
Shall I make us some hot chocolate? Yes, please!
I wonder why she loves to work so much.
I mean, it wasn't always her dream to work for that company, was it?
Hmm... It isn't so much that Mom enjoys her work...
What she really likes is trying her best at something.
Even though she encounters lots of trying and unpleasant things...
...the satisfaction she gets from overcoming those challenges...
...is what she treasures most in this world.
So even though working at a company wasn't necessarily her dream...
...the way she is living her life is absolutely ideal to her.
It's possible to achieve your dreams in that way as well, you know.
So the way she lives her life was her dream?
Different people might have different opinions of that...
But as for me, that's something I really love about her. I respect the way she leads her life and am very proud of her.
She truly is amazing, isn't she?
That you're leading innocent bystanders into real danger?
You're trying to lead them so that they want to be magical girls.
And you don't like that, I take it? No. It's a problem.
...Particularly in the case of Madoka Kaname.
I see. So you've noticed it as well, have you? That she has incredible potential.
She is the one person I absolutely cannot allow to make the contract.
Afraid that a magical girl stronger than you will get in your way? That's the way a bullied child thinks.
I have no wish to fight you, but...
Then take care to ensure that our paths will never cross again.
Tonight will probably be the last time... ...that we will be able to speak without coming to blows.
Huh? Weren't you able to see Kamijo today?
Apparently, he couldn't be inconvenienced to see me today or something.
Seriously, after I took all the trouble to come here. How rude!
A Grief Seed! It's about to hatch!
No way! Why here of all places?
This isn't good. We have to get out of here!
A Labyrinth is about to open up here!
You mean one of those crazy mazes?!
Madoka, do you have Mami's phone number on you?
This isn't good... Madoka, find Mami and bring her here.
I'll stay here and keep an eye on that thing.
That's too dangerous. Though there's still time before the witch emerges, once the labyrinth pulls you inside, you won't be able to leave it.
There's no guarantee that Mami will get here in time to save you.
But once the labyrinth opens, we'll lose track of the witch, won't we?
I can't afford to let that happen. Not here...
Huh? Once Mami gets here, she'll be able to track my position using telepathy.
So if I stay and watch the Grief Seed with Sayaka, I'll be able to guide Mami...
...down the shortest path to us. Thank you, Kyubey!
Then, I'll find Mami and bring her here as fast as I can!
Well, yeah... that kind of goes without saying.
If you were just to decide upon a wish...
...I could turn you into a magical girl right here and now.
Right. If things get bad enough, I may ask you to do that.
But I'll hold off for now.
Because this is such an important decision to me...
...I don't want to make it rashly if possible.
It looks like the witch isn't going to hatch just yet.
Sayaka, are you okay? Totally fine.
I'm so bored I'm about to doze off in here! Right now, it'd be better not to use any large amounts of magic that might disturb the egg.
There's no need to hurry, so come to us as quietly as you can. Got it.
Thank goodness we made it in time.
Though Sayaka took such a huge risk that I'm actually a bit angry...
But in this one case, it was a good, clear-headed call on her part.
This way, we won't have to worry about the witch getting a-
I thought I told you I didn't want to see you again.
The two of you should leave here.
I don't think so. Miki and Kyubey are waiting for us in there.
And you think we could trust you?
This isn't the time for- I don't want to hurt you, of course.
But if you insist on struggling, the cords will only tighten.
This witch is not like the others!
Behave and I will release you unharmed after I finish up here.
What is it? I've been thinking really hard about all sorts of different wishes, but...
Did you decide on one? Yes.
But, I think it might be the nave kind of wish that would make you mad...
So what is this dream you want granted?
Well, I've never been good at school, and I don't have any kind of talent that I could take pride in...
And I'm sure I'll continue on like this, being no use to anyone and having to bother others for help...
Thinking about that makes me feel so awful, I can't stand it.
But then I met you, Mami.
And you showed me what it's like...
And then... ...when I heard that even I might be able to do the same thing...
...it was the happiest thing I'd ever experienced in my life.
That's why, I think that just becoming a magical girl would fulfill my dreams.
If someone like me can help people and live my life with pride... That would be my greatest dream.
It won't be easy, you know?
You'll get injured, and you won't have time to go on dates or have fun with friends.
Even so, after watching the way you keep doing your very best...
...I really look up to you, Mami.
I'm really not worth looking up to.
Huh? I only pretend to be cool. I'm really pushing myself hard.
Even when I'm scared, or hurting, there's no one I can talk to.
All I can do is cry on my own.
It isn't a good thing... to be a magical girl.
But you're not alone any more, Mami.
You're right... I'm not alone anymore, am I?
Will you really stand and fight with me from now on?
Will you really stay with me?
Yes. If someone like me will do.
Some role model I'm supposed to be.
I'm really no good at this, am I?
